quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  54,7,"with their sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i><i class=""s"">(subdued) </i>in reverence they come out of the tombs like swarming locusts,"
  54,8,"scrambling towards the Summoner; the deniers say, “This is a hard day.”"
  54,9,"The people of Noah disbelieved before them, so they disbelieved Our servant and said, “A madman!”, and he was rebuked."
  54,10,"So he called upon his Lord, “I am overcome, so bestow help!”"
  54,11,"So We <span class=""h"">opened<sup foot_note=""81242"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>the gates of the sky with water pouring down,"
  54,12,"and We made the earth burst with springs, so the waters met for a matter already determined."
  54,13,"And We carried him on a craft of planks and nails,"
  54,14,"sailing before Our eyes—a repayment for the one who had been denied."
  54,15,"And most surely We have left it as a sign, so is there anyone to remind himself?"
  54,16,"So how were My punishment and My warnings!"
  54,17,"And most surely We have made the Recital{1}easy for remembrance, so is there anyone to remind himself?",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  54,18,"ʻĀd{1}disbelieved, so how were My punishment and My warnings!",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Hûd.
  54,19,"Indeed, We sent against them a screaming wind on a day of unrelenting misfortune,"
  54,20,"plucking people away as though they were trunks of uprooted palm trees."
  54,21,"So how were My punishment and My warnings!"
  54,22,"And most surely We made the Recital<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>easy for remembrance, so is there anyone to remind himself?"
  54,23,"Thamûd{1}disbelieved in the warnings",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Salih.
  54,24,"and said, “Are we to follow a human being from among us? Indeed, we would then be astray and insane!"
  54,25,"Has the Reminder been cast to him out of all of us? Rather, he is a wicked sheer liar.”"
  54,26,"<span class=""h"">They<sup foot_note=""81246"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">will know</span>tomorrow who the wicked sheer liar is."
  54,27,"We are sending the she-camel as a means of trial for them, so watch<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>them and be patient."
